# UI/UX and Polish Rules

Mythora should feel polished without requiring a large art team.

Design direction:
- premium mobile UI
- readable battle board
- reusable panels and cards
- restrained animations
- strong feedback on matches and skills
- minimal bespoke environment art

Avoid:
- expensive animated scenes
- large handcrafted maps
- complex character animation systems
- UI that depends on many custom illustrations
- over-designed screens that slow down iteration

Battle screen priorities:
1. board readability
2. clear moves remaining
3. clear AP/resource meters
4. obvious available skills
5. visible enemy intent
6. fast turn resolution
7. satisfying but short animations

Use reusable design components:
- resource chip
- hero card
- skill button
- enemy intent badge
- reward card
- item tooltip
- status effect badge
- rarity frame

Mobile constraints:
- design for one-handed play where possible
- avoid tiny tap targets
- support small phone screens
- respect safe areas
- avoid text overflow
